## ⚠️ Read this before believing any phase numbering

Two unrelated phase systems live in this codebase. Confusing them has caused
agents to either rebuild already-shipped work or skip ahead.

| Naming | What it actually refers to | Authoritative status |
|---|---|---|
| **Product Phases 0–5** (Jordan's strategic roadmap) | Phase 0 = routing split. Phase 1 = activation funnel. Phase 2 = device/country SEO. Phase 3 = brand homepage. Phase 4 = help/blog. Phase 5 = in-app physical SIM checkout. | Phase 0 ✅ done. **Phase 1 ✅ shipped (renamed "Activation Funnel" — see below)**. Phase 2-5 not started. |
| **"Activation Funnel"** (what Phase 1 was renamed to on 2026-04-25) | Same scope as the original product Phase 1, renamed to avoid the collision below. | `docs/ACTIVATION_FUNNEL.md` is single source of truth. Steps 1-7 all shipped across H5/Laravel/admin/Flutter. |
| **China-team backend phases** (commit prefixes like `feat(phase1):`, `feat(phase2):`) | Backend migration work owned by the China dev team. Their `phase1` = supplier-package backend migration. Their `phase2` = token-refresh interceptor + cross-platform contract. UNRELATED to Jordan's product phases. | Their phase 0A/0B/0C/0D and phase 1 are shipped. Their phase 2 just shipped 2026-04-25. |

Whenever you see "Phase 1" in a doc/commit/comment, **disambiguate which system
the author meant before acting**.

### Reference docs (with their respective scope)

- `docs/ACTIVATION_FUNNEL.md` — current source of truth for what was shipped.
- `.cursor/rules/product-decisions.mdc` — long-term product decisions (also lists
  Phase 0–5 in §"Phase order"; same "Phase 1 = activation funnel" naming, accurate
  for what _was originally_ scoped under that label).

## Active thread: Phase 2 — cross-platform consolidation

After auditing the China team's Flutter `feature/evairsim-jordan` branch
(25+ commits we don't have, full native app + Reverb live chat) we kept
our WebView-shell direction and ported the *patterns* worth keeping
without merging any of their code. Outcomes shipped 2026-04-25:

1. **H5 axios token-refresh interceptor** (`services/api/client.ts`):
   - Now accepts both `code: 0` (legacy `/h5/*`) and `code: '200'`/`'201'`
     (new `/v1/app/*`) as success via the new `isSuccessApiCode()`
     helper. Closed a latent prod bug — the old `body.code !== 0` check
     would have thrown ApiError on every successful `bindSim`,
     `setupIntent`, `setAutoRenew` call. The Activation Funnel smoke
     test only exercised the preview path which kept the legacy shape.
   - Refresh now hits `/v1/app/auth/refresh` instead of legacy
     `/h5/auth/refresh` (both write to `user_tokens` so legacy tokens
     keep working).
   - Single-flight queue: N parallel 401s coalesce into one refresh.
   - 11 vitest cases in `services/api/client.test.ts` covering both
     conventions, parallel 401s, refresh failure, endpoint correctness.
2. **`docs/CROSS_PLATFORM_CONTRACT.md`** — single source of truth for
   what crosses the H5 ↔ Flutter ↔ Laravel boundary. Pins response
   envelope, error namespace, auth flow, channel auth, chat REST + WS
   contract, message-type metadata payloads, dedup keys, versioning
   policy. Edit here whenever you change a wire-format field.
3. **Laravel `MessageSent::broadcastWith()`** — extended to include
   `message_type`, `media_url`, `metadata` so the WS payload mirrors
   the REST `ChatMessageResource`. The Flutter team's "fetch via REST
   after every WS event" workaround can be retired whenever they pull.

Deferred (intentional):

- **H5 chat module**: the actual `LiveChatPage.tsx` + `useChat()` hook
  + `services/api/chat.ts` + bottom-sheet pickers. Estimated 3-5 days
  of focused work. Decision: hold until Activation Funnel has live
  traffic and we know it's healthy. Customers can email
  `service@evairdigital.com` for support during the rollout — Resend
  routes those.
- **Flutter aliyun branch sync**: their `feature/evairsim-jordan` has
  25+ commits we don't have. Our local `main` deletes files they
  modified (because of our WebView shell pivot). User decided to ask
  the China team to rebase their work on top of our WebView shell, so
  we don't merge anything from their side. The save-all.sh now pushes
  Flutter to `feature/jordan-webview-shell` on Aliyun (renamed in
  `EvairSIM-App/scripts/save.sh`) so we no longer collide.

